Tobe Carberry playing and coaching timeline

1996 - 2000

Played basketball at the University of Vermont

2000 - 2001

Played for the Cork Blue Demons in Ireland

Played for the Brooklyn Kings in the United States Basketball League

2001

Drafted by the North Charleston Lowgators in the NBA G-League, formerly known as the NBA Development League

2002

2003 - 2004

Played for the Asheville Altitude in the NBA G-League

2005 - 2006

Played for Worthersee Piraten in Austria

2006 - 2007

Played for Sopron KC in Hungary

2007 - 2010

Assistant coach at Southern Connecticut State University

Assistant coach at the University of New Haven

2010 - 2014

2014 - 2016

Assistant coach at Central Connecticut State University

2016

Founded Haven4Hoops

2016 - 2017

Assistant coach at Long Island University, Brooklyn

2017 - 2020

Assistant coach at Yale

2020 - present

Assistant coach at Columbia

Sources: Sports Reference College Basketball, Basketball Reference, Piraten, Eurobasket, Long Island University Brooklyn Blackbirds, gocolumbialions.com, interview with Tobe Carberry
